defs.docs:
A crate that provides facilities for testing the approximate equality of floating-point
 based types, using either relative difference, or units in the last place (ULPs)
 comparisons.

defs.name: AbsDiffEq
defs.docs: Equality that is defined using the absolute difference of two numbers.

defs.name: Epsilon
defs.docs: Used for specifying relative comparisons.

defs.name: default_epsilon
defs.docs: The default tolerance to use when testing values that are close together.

defs.name: abs_diff_eq
defs.docs:
A test for equality that uses the absolute difference to compute the approximate
 equality of two numbers.

defs.name: abs_diff_ne
defs.docs: The inverse of `ApproxEq::abs_diff_eq`.

defs.name: RelativeEq
defs.docs:
Equality comparisons between two numbers using both the absolute difference and
 relative based comparisons.

defs.name: default_max_relative
defs.docs: The default relative tolerance for testing values that are far-apart.

defs.name: relative_eq
defs.value: fn (&self, other: &Rhs, epsilon: Self::Epsilon, max_relative: Self::Epsilon) -> bool
defs.docs: A test for equality that uses a relative comparison if the values are far apart.

defs.name: relative_ne
defs.value: fn (&self, other: &Rhs, epsilon: Self::Epsilon, max_relative: Self::Epsilon) -> bool
defs.docs: The inverse of `ApproxEq::relative_eq`.

defs.name: UlpsEq
defs.docs:
Equality comparisons between two numbers using both the absolute difference and ULPs
 (Units in Last Place) based comparisons.

defs.name: default_max_ulps
defs.docs: The default ULPs to tolerate when testing values that are far-apart.

defs.name: ulps_eq
defs.value: fn (&self, other: &Rhs, epsilon: Self::Epsilon, max_ulps: u32) -> bool
defs.docs: A test for equality that uses units in the last place (ULP) if the values are far apart.

defs.name: ulps_ne
defs.value: fn (&self, other: &Rhs, epsilon: Self::Epsilon, max_ulps: u32) -> bool
defs.docs: The inverse of `ApproxEq::ulps_eq`.
